The paper focuses on object classification and detection using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of weak supervisions and multiple instance learning also suggests a potential fit for machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
